 Sanjhbela

 Separated from her husband, the matron of a hospital finds her life at the crossroads with the arrival of a stranger. The Bimal Kar story features director Meghnad Bhattacharya and Swatilekha Sengupta.

 Catch it at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm, July 6

 Antarjali Jatra

 Gobardanga Shilpayan stages Kamal Kumar Mazumder?s literary masterpiece about a teenaged girl being married off to a dying old man. Directed by Ashis Chattopadhyay. 

 Catch it at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm, July 2

 Kanan Pishir Jwapomala

 A glimpse into the plight of 19th century widows through the eyes of two teenaged girls. Presented by theatre group Illusion, the play is directed by Suranjana Dasgupta.

 Catch it at Madhusudan Mancha, 6.30 pm, July 3




